Detailed Description

template<class H, class E, class K, class T>
struct hashbase< H, E, K, T >

A specializable hash base class for the creation of hash tables and other objects.

Implemented via the hash chaining method; there are DEFAULTSIZE chains that can have multiple elements in the case of a hash collision, connected by a single directional linked list. The base size of the hash table is fixed at the construction of the hash table and cannot be changed later.

Note that E (the element type being stored) and T (the type that gets added) are not necessarily the same.

Template Parameters
HThe inheriting object
EThe type of the element type to be stored
Kthe type of the element's key
Tthe type of the data being added
